      "content": "MACRS depreciation for a 7-year property class can be calculated using the Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System (MACRS) tables. The formula is:\n\nDepreciation = (Cost of Asset - Residual Value) / Useful Life\n\nFor a 7-year property class, the depreciation rates for the first year are:\n\n* 100% in the first year (no depreciation, as it's fully depreciated in the first year)\n* 100% in the second year (another 100% depreciation)\n* 83.33% in the third year\n* 50% in the fourth year\n* 41.67% in the fifth year\n* 25% in the sixth year\n* 20% in the seventh year\n\nYou can use these rates to calculate the depreciation for the first year. However, it's worth noting that the equipment's residual value is not specified, so you'll need to estimate or obtain the actual residual value to calculate the depreciation.\n\nFor example, if the cost of the equipment is $100,000 and the residual value is $20,000, the depreciation for the first year would be:\n\nDepreciation = ($100,000 - $20,000) / 7 =",
